codex
I have enough context to patch the verifier now. Plan:
1. Replace the heuristic victim picker with a victim-level scan that prefers the address with the largest immediately withdrawable ERC20 value.
2. Make the owner-stage proof explicit at runtime: `initialize()` takeover if uninitialized, direct `recoverAssets` if already owner, otherwise constrained probing of the live owner contract’s public call surface and a concrete failure reason when that stage is unreachable.
3. Preserve the exact exploit sequence in code comments, withdraw only reassigned matured ERC20 locks, and keep profit accounting strictly to pre-existing on-chain tokens.
codex
I’m replacing the verifier now. The edit keeps the exploit path fixed and makes the failure mode explicit when `onlyOwner` cannot be satisfied by any public on-chain route at the fork.
